 the words “in the area which is subject to the jurisdiction of such State or Indian tribe” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b)(1), before clause (A), the words “Not later than 18 months after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-16"},"text":"November 16, 1990","children":[],"tail":"” are omitted as obsolete. In clause (H)(i), the words “prescribed under this subsection” are added for clarity."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (d)(1), the words “within 18 months of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-16"},"text":"November 16, 1990","children":[],"tail":"” are omitted as obsolete. The words “over a matter” are omitted as surplus."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (d)(3), the word “civil” is added for consistency in the revised title and with other titles of the United States Code.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (e), the words “superseding or otherwise”, “application of”, “relating to vehicle weight limitations”, and “relating to vehicle length and vehicle width limitations, respectively” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (f), the word “modify” is omitted as surplus and for consistency in the revised title. The words “issued by the Department of Transportation before ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-16"},"text":"November 16, 1990","children":[],"tail":", and” are omitted as obsolete."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idca8ebcd4-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idca8ebcd5-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2012—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/141"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–141","children":[],"tail":" designated existing provisions as par. (1), inserted heading, and added par. (2)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2005—Subsec. (a)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/59"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–59","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Secretary” for “Secretary of Transportation” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idca8ebcd6-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idca8ebcd7-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2012 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/141"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–141","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2012-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 2012","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/141/s3/a"},"text":"section 3(a) of Pub. L. 112–141","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective and Termination Dates of 2012 Amendment note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t23/s101"},"text":"section 101 of Title 23","children":[],"tail":", Highways."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idca8ebcd8-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Study of Hazardous Materials Transportation by Motor Carriers Near Federal Prisons","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/311/tI/s121"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–311, title I, § 121","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-08-26"},"text":"Aug. 26, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/1681"},"text":"108 Stat. 1681","children":[],"tail":", directed Secretary of Transportation to submit to Congress, not later than 1 year after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-08-26"},"text":"Aug. 26, 1994","children":[],"tail":", report on results of study to determine safety considerations of transporting hazardous materials by motor carriers in close proximity to Federal prisons, particularly those housing maximum security prisoners, which was to include evaluation of ability of such facilities and designated local planning agencies to safely evacuate such prisoners in event of emergency and any special training, equipment, or personnel that would be required by such facility and designated local emergency planning agencies to carry out such evacuation."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
